 his memoir, Beneath the Underdog, the famous Tijuana episodes, his relationships, and the jazz business.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aJazz musiciansvInterviews. 0aMingus, Charles. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Jazz.2bisacsh  aamerican culture.  abass players.  abig band.  abiographies.  abiography.  ablack music.  acandid interviews.  acharles mingus.  aengaging.  aentertainment industry.  aentertainment.  ahistorical.  ahistory.  ahumor.  ain depth interviews.  ainterviews.  ajazz age.  ajazz business.  ajazz composers.  ajazz greats.  ajazz music.  ajazz musicians.  ajournalism.  alive entertainment.  amusic history.  apage turner.  aperformance arts.  arace.  arelationships.  asocial issues.  atijuana episodes.  aus history.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095468740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520954687423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520954687/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles